data.title: This place is closed.
data.text: Used to be a bar and restaurant, but is closed and under new ownership. It is now completely remodeled and is in operation as the upscale restaurant "KOL"

data.title: Shamrock in our Guinness
data.text: Clean, comfortable and good customer service. Our lunch- sandwiches, was delicious, portions were huge.  My husband ordered a Guinness and the bartender had made in shamrock in the foam while pouring it.  I would recommend this place for a lunch or casual dinner.

data.title: Was a great place when we first moved here.
data.text: When we first got here, this place was amazing. Had great food and even a rare beer my hubby liked. Now its under new ownership and its a horrible place to go to! Its all gloomy inside now, Hubby's favorite beer is gone and the food sucks! They should of kept it the same!

data.title: Great time and service
data.text: A few weeks ago a few friends of mine and I went to Dublin's for the first time since it changed owners. Wow what an amazing change! It looks amazing inside and out. The bar tenders did a great job making our drinks. There was a short girl that made sure we always had drinks she was great making sure we were happy and had a good time. To top it off we watched the most talented and friendly  guys we have ever seen carry towers of empty glasses n glasses with drinks n ice making sure the tables were clean and free of empty glasses n beer bottles and he did it while moving from table dodging people and he to made sure we were having a great time which we did. If you haven't been there you got to go check it out! Thank you to the bar tenders the waitress and the glass guy for an amazing time!

data.title: Never on a Sunday?
data.text: Hoped to be welcomed on Sunday evening but hostile staff told us they were closing at 9pm with no reason given .  I assume it was because we were English.

data.title: Don't go there
data.text: This place is a joke!  Horrible food and service!  The door people are horrendous!  Stay away!  You been warned!

data.title: The Whovians Rejoice!
data.text:
I was so excited and pleased to find out last week that Dublin Square was going to show the 50th Anniversary of Doctor Who at 5pm, not knowing how many were coming, just that people were coming.  After we got there, and conversing with the few employees that were on, I find that management's logic on how many were expected and how many to have on for the night was greatly flawed.  There were nearly 30 of us - JUST WHOVIANS - a more than half of us in cosplay.  From the TARDIS, to the Doctor (pick one), my son as The Master, my as a Red Dalek (wielding a plunger (clean) and whisk), it was a great time!  Originally, we were going to be seated in the back area of the bar by the pool tables, but something happened with the TV (The TARDIS broke it) and so whatever was on the big screen was changed for the group of us that were there.  Which was really awesome!  It allowed us to spread out, commingle, and go between tables and such to meet others we hadn't met before.

Johnny and Sherise (forgive the spelling if it's wrong) were fantastic!  The drinks and food were slow in coming, but it's not like we weren't all going to be there for 2 hours!  Being pub food, it was average, but it still came out hot and was still tasty!  I think there MIGHT have been one other employee I saw every now and then (the cook?) who helped with delivering food items to various tables.  I apologized in advance for bringing a few outside food items for my picky two year old - and Johnny was extremely gracious about it - completely understood, as he has kids himself.

We've already been told we are welcome to come back - and we will certainly be happy to come back again in the future!

GERONIMO!!!!

data.title: Outdoor seating and a cold Beer!
data.text: This was just what we were looking for after a long day of sight-seeing and travel. We stopped at this Irish pub downtown Rapid City for a recommended Rueben --  which was very, very good. Plenty of food! The day and time we were there it was fairly quiet -- which was fine with us...we were looking to be outside. It was your average pub with good food and good service.  After dinner, we walked further down the street and the Firehouse Pub was filled and overflowing with people - inside and out.

data.title: Eating in Rapid City
data.text: This is pub grub so don't expect haute cuisine, but the food was very good, the service was excellent and the price was very economical. A very important consideration when you are on a budget.

data.title: Nice food--nice atmosphere!
data.text: We were staying in a hotel across the street from Dublin Square so we thought to try it.  All we had were drinks and salad--BUT--what a salad it was--absolutely a meal in itself!  Friends with us raved about the pizza!

data.title: Fish Taco was very good!
data.text: The Dublin Squares fish taco was very, very good.  Service was also very good.  The music was not traditional for an Irish Pub, but was rock and was a bit too loud for our taste.  Overall, I would go back for the taco!

data.title: A Bar but not a Pub
data.text: We ate at this pub our first of two evenings in Rapid City.  We chose it mainly because of its proximity to the Adoba Hotel across the street, and because the menu seemed full and attractive enough to handle the tastes of the 3 couples.  In fact, the ambiance is more like a basic bar than of a pub.  I had fish and chips, which was ok.  Others ended up having pizza, and weren't particularly happy with their choice.  The service was ok, but nothing special.  Mostly, we were hoping for a bit cheerier ambiance, and this restaurant did not compare well with out second night's meal or with suggestions from others in our group about other nearby pubs.

data.title: Just a bar
data.text: Friendly, but the food was below average.This place looked like it was be remodeled with chairs and tables stacked in the corners.The bartender was also the server and the best thing about this place.

data.title: great place to party
data.text: Outstanding beer selection. excellent live band. my only complaint was that staff failed to eject a patron that was clearly antagonizing other patrons because he appeared to be friends with a bouncer.the food here as great as well.

data.title: Very good
data.text: The restaurant has good service and a great Reuben sandwich and cold beer. The prices were very good. We were there early in the evening so seating Was easy to find however things seem to be getting much busier when we left.

data.title: Nice Little Irish Pub
data.text:
Stopped in to get out of the rain for a drink and some music.
Very nice little pub in the heart of town not far from our hotel.
Good piped in music.

data.title: Perfect location and cold beer
data.text: The bar is on a corner and has garage doors that open on both sides of the corner so you get a full view of both streets. Our waitress was fantastic but had to take care of the entire bar by herself and it was a Thursday night with street concerts downtown. Prices are lower than on Main and worth walking two blocks.

data.title: Food
data.text: The irish ruben sandwich was the best I have ever had. great friendly service. would recomend this to anyone

data.title: Highly recommend
data.text: We had a great meal here, hope your as lucky as us. We had fish, burger, pizza. Great portion and well cooked , The waiter Matt excellent was not pushy a great server and the best value for your money. The place has a great atmosphere and would go back.

data.title: Night out with the hubby
data.text: This place has a very nice atmosphere to it. A place to go visit friends or just to have a night to yourself. All their prices are very reasonable and they have a very good assortment of food and drinks. They have plenty of room if you have a big group so that was a nice touch.
